Question: What type of cultural arts or entertainment opportunities would you like to see more of in Austin?

Response ID: resp_2853
Response Text: OUTDOOR plays and events that are FOR Austin and BY Austin and NOT like ACL which should get the hell out of Zilker already, learning opportunities (camps/classes) for filmmakers, playwrights, actors, writers, sound engineers, lighting engineers and all of the supporting arts for the flashier stars, all types of assistance and learning on the business side of managing a career in the arts. Honestly, spend just one year promoting arts outside of Antone's and the Continental Club and maybe we'll get somewhere. For my money, I don't see that we need a lot more rock n roll here. For one thing, the kids don't even like rock n roll and my performing musician friends say no one comes out anymore anyway. Classical music, dixieland jazz... I mean, let's try a few new channels, if you get my drift. New channels in new places, outdoor, free, FREE, FREE, but not on the ACL model. Do it on the Zilker Hillside Model and you get my vote.

